# OpenAI Codex SDK Playbook

Copy this folder into the root of a project where Codex will help integrate Caracal SDKs.

This setup mirrors the Claude Code and GitHub Copilot SDK playbooks. It makes Codex understand the product, user needs, and architecture first, confirm the plan with the user, then integrate Caracal with official SDK APIs and minimal native changes.

## Use

1. Copy `.codex/` into your project root.
2. Configure Codex to read `.codex/AGENTS.md` and `.codex/config.toml`.
3. Start with product discovery, architecture review, SDK/version selection, and integration planning.
4. Implement only after the user confirms the proposed approach.

## Contents

- `.codex/AGENTS.md`: primary operating guide containing senior Platform Engineer instructions, discovery guidelines, planning and implementation rules.
- `.codex/config.toml`: documentation, MCP, approval, and safety configuration.

Do not paste raw provider secrets into chat. Use redacted values or environment variable names.
